They see Miley, Rihanna and Beyonce and try to emulate them through nothing better than impromptu dances on Instagram! Why? Based on the same jaded notion of, "if you don't listen to my rules you will not be popular."

Mentality Beyond the Rules: This brings us to the "Mentality Beyond the Rules;" for example, the Roots International Finishing School in Kingston. Created by Leighton Scott, Boss Tom, Candace Morano and May-le Vale CarMad.

The goal of the program was simple: show the students of Tredegar Park E.A. basic professionalism and appropriate etiquette. Board of Director member Mrs. Ingrid Goodison Brown said that 70% of the training covered was attitude and manners. The students were trained on topics like the importance of neatness, the meaning of decorum, and how to present themselves in a communal atmosphere. The teachers were briefed extensively on how to convince the students that these skills were fundamental, to not only their academic lives but also their careers. The classes were illustrated by examples of the importance of correcting professors with; "Yes Mme, No Mme, and Thank You Mme”!
